      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 22
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust 1993 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) featuring the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW rotary engine. This platform retains its factory-spec induction system, delivering a seamless transition between primary and secondary boost phases. The chassis benefits from a 50/50 weight distribution and a sophisticated four-wheel double-wishbone suspension, ensuring exceptional lateral grip and communicative steering feedback. Power is delivered through a precise five-speed manual gearbox to a Torsen limited-slip differential. Recent service includes a cooling system refresh and vacuum line inspection to ensure peak thermal efficiency and boost stability. While the aesthetics reflect honest road use, the drivetrain remains a testament to high-revving Japanese engineering, making this a prime candidate for a driver-centric collection.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 22
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_11_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_11",
      "description": "Well-maintained. Clean title. Minor cosmetic wear. Engine runs smooth. Service records available.",
